Abdul Hannan's beautifully sung pleading about the life we live which is like shattered glass the falseness the lies the confused thoughts and then the incredibly deep response by Jafar guiding to the truth of the inner self reflection. Thank you Coke Studio. Finally going back to the true values of the spiritual nature of our music.

If we could find out who wrote the lyrics, composed the piece, who were the musicians that would be wonderful. Don't forget this is a record for posterity.

snippet.textDisplay: Coke Studio Pakistan, you've touched our hearts in a way that's beyond words! Your dedication to showcasing the beauty of South Asian culture is nothing short of magical. With every beat, every note, every visual, you've woven a tapestry of emotions that resonates deeply with all of us. It's like you've taken our collective memories, dreams, and aspirations, and set them to music. In a world where it's easy to feel lost in the shuffle of Western influences, you've given us a reason to stand tall and proud of our roots. Your passion and creativity have turned 'eastern' into the new definition of cool, and that's a feat worthy of applause and admiration. You've not only revived our culture but also made it a beacon of hope and inspiration for generations to come. From the bottom of our hearts, we send you all our love and support. Keep creating those soul-stirring masterpieces that make us smile, cry, and feel connected to something bigger than ourselves. You've earned a special place in our hearts, Coke Studio Pakistan, and we're forever grateful for the beauty you've brought into our lives.
